news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Major relaxations proposed in development scheme
news.para: Kovalam-Vizhinjam area development scheme had earlier been varied in 2010. It covers a total area of 1907.50 ha.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh: Infrastructure worth Rs 33,000 crore to come up in housing layouts
news.para: The BEEP, a bilateral cooperation project between the Union Ministry of Power and the Swiss government, is being implemented by the Bureau of Energy Efficiency in coordination with APSECM.

news.title: EV charging station makers see rise in demand from realtors
news.para: "The EV market has been growing on the back of a government push. But now more people also want to move to environmentally friendly modes of transportation, and that's visible from the demand we are getting from housing societies and RWAs, " said Sumit Dhanuka, founder, ElectriVa, a leading EV charging startup.

news.title: NHB seeking agency for data collection on unsold residential units across 50 cities
news.para: The housing finance regulator publishes two HPIs -- HPI@ Assessment Prices and HPI@ Market Prices for Under Construction Properties for 50 cities.

news.title: Centre prepares plan to check out of Ashok Hotel
news.para: Although the government is seeking to complete the process at the earliest, the entire transaction is unlikely to be completed in the current financial year.

news.title: Rupert Murdoch buys 340,000-acre ranch for $200 million from Koch dynasty
news.para: Murdoch bought the property from Matador Cattle Co., a unit of Koch Industries. The deal is the largest ranch sale in Montana history, and comes about 70 years after Fred Koch, founder of the crude oil company that would later become Koch Industries, originally bought it.

news.title: Need for steps like ease of capital, property tax relief to promote rental housing projects: CBRE
news.para: To unlock the potential of the rental housing segment, CBRE said the government has already launched Affordable Rental Housing Complex (ARHC) scheme and also brought the Model Tenancy Act, 2021, but felt that "a lot more remains to be done".

news.title: Lulu Group to invest Rs 2,000 crore to build shopping mall in Gujarat
news.para: The Lulu Group already has three operational malls in India and will open two more mall in the country by March next year. "The Lulu Group will invest Rs 2,000 crore in the state of Gujarat to set up a modern shopping mall," the company said.

news.title: China's Fantasia Holdings denies creditor claim on unit's shares
news.para: TFI Securities and Futures Ltd told Fantasia it was entitled to enforce the charge of 780 million shares in the unit, Colour Life Services Group, Fantasia said in a filing to the Hong Kong stock exchange late on Friday.

news.title: Odisha CM demands 1.84 lakh houses for Fani hit families under PMAY-Gramin
news.para: ​Patnaik in a letter thanked the prime minister for sanctioning 8.17 Lakh PMAY(G) houses to Odisha while drawing his attention to the woes of many families of KBK (Kalahandi-Bolangir-Koraput) region and tribal dominated districts of the state and many families who have lost their houses in cyclone Fani in 2019.

news.title: Demand for dedicated Karnataka-Rera secretary grows as compensation cases pile up
news.para: Karnataka Real Estate Regulatory Authority (K-Rera) listed 120 apartment projects whose promoters have failed to deliver flats within the agreed date.

news.title: Haryana CM promise permanent electricity connections to 13 societies
news.para: According to the CM, a policy has been worked upon and supply of connections will start latest by December 21. Khattar said the electrical department will try to recover the money from the builders, and the builders will also call a meeting.

news.title: Mumbai: NCDRC directs Hetali Enterprises to pay Rs 34 lakh to buyers for smaller flat
news.para: The amount includes the market value of Rs 24,650 (2016) per sqft, along with 9% interest. The commission also directed the builder to pay a total of Rs 30 lakh for mental agony and compensation for a delay of eight months in handing over possession and costs of litigation.

news.title: Builders protest Mhada's 'rigged' redevelopment tender for Motilal Nagar
news.para: Mhada has inserted a clause stating only developers with a net worth of not less than Rs 9,000 crore as on March 31, 2021, can qualify. TOI has learned that two top developers, Godrej Properties and Prestige Group, have shot off protest letters to Mhada.

news.title: Gujarat RERA directs Bhanushri Realties to pay compensation to home buyer
news.para: The case involved Gaurav Desai who had purchased a flat in Maruti Amrakunj-2, a scheme floated by Bhanushri Realties, for Rs 30 lakh. According to Desai, he faced delayed possession by five months and use of substandard material in construction.
